\pard\nowidctlpar\cf5\lang1033\f1\fs32 J\f0  \cf4\ul HOW TO PLAY\par
\pard\ri-7\keepn\nowidctlpar\tx8647\cf0\lang1048\ulnone\fs24 The idea behind this game is extremely simple: you, a pedestrian, have to cross a street and a river while avoiding the hazards such as cars, motorcycles, boats, waves and alligators. If you get hit by one of these, an ambulance will come and save you in the nick of time (this means that the action doesn\rquote t take place in Romania, heh heh\'85) and you will be returned to the bottom of the screen to try again. \b However\b0 , you can only be saved 5 times. If you get hit and have no chances left (shown on the bottom of the screen), well\'85 \ldblquote Sorry, we did all we could\'85\rdblquote  Anyway, when you get to the other side, a bonus is given to you based on the time you took to get there, and then you start again on the bottom of the screen in the next, more difficult level. In D.C.M. SOFT\rquote s new version, many surprises will await you as you progress trough the levels, so keep an eye out for these!\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\lang1033\fs20\par
\cf6\f1\fs32 7\cf5\f0  \cf4\ul CONTROLS\par
\cf2\ulnone\fs24 You can control the pedestrian \b only \b0 with the keyboard, and access higher game functions (such as New game, Options, etc.) with the keyboard or mouse. Joystick control is not implemented. Press the \b left arrow\b0  or the \b right arrow\b0  keys to step to the left or right and the \b up arrow\b0  and \b down arrow\b0  to move forwards or backwards. If the game area wrap option is ON, exiting trough the left or right side of the screen will cause you to appear on the other side (it is assumed that the road and river are somehow \ldblquote circular\rdblquote ), if it\rquote s not then you won\rquote t be allowed to move outside the playing region. The commands and options you can access trough the menus should be self-explainatory, so they won\rquote t be discussed here. And, by the way, the game automatically pauses when you work with something outside the game window or when you click on any of the pull-down menus.\par
