\cf2\f1\fs32 :\f0  \cf4\ul PROGRAMMER'S INFO\par
\cf2\ulnone\fs24 If you\rquote re just an ordinary user and you don\rquote t belong to the strange world of programming, you can skip this section, \lquote cause I\rquote ll be talking both in English and in Borland Pascal\'99. The main program was written by D.C.M. SOFT in about a week (the graphics and documents took longer to build) and used a freeware MCI-interfacing unit. As you would expect, the main window uses its own device context (thus speeding up graphic output by 30%) and intercepts several windows messages. It would have been possible to implement a special sound interface which allows multiple wave sounds (and possible WaveTable emulation \lang1024\f1 J\lang1033\f0 )  if it weren\rquote t for Windows\'99\rquote s paranoia which doesn\rquote t let me change the speed of the timer interrupt. I\rquote d sure like to find out how port-intercepting is done, though\'85 \par
